The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, January 07, 2004 				 When small is wonderful
																								Creativity is in itself a process of learning. It enables an observer to peer into the innermost essence of things and ponder over the universe in constant upheaval. This inward turmoil is felt, interpreted and revealed to us by artists as they explore myriad ways of communicating their experiences. In a way, their exploration of the creative universe is a progression on a metaphysical level. Vikalp Art Shop is currently hosting an exhibition of paintings by four of Bengals contemporary masters: Paritosh Sen, Rabin Mondal, Prakash Karmakar and Sanat Kar. Immensely respected by both connoisseurs of art and critics for their profound contribution to modern art, the artists have now ventured to greener pastures. They have expressed themselves on small canvases. Restricting oneself to pre-defined small frames has its own limitations, but it is amazing to see how the artists have overcome their difficulties and created Small Wonders  beautiful creations that are a kind of revelation for viewers.																								When: Till January 15; 2 pm - 8 pm																								Where: Vikalp Art Shop, Swabhumi
